---
// The Challenge section for Trade & Field Services industry page
---

<section id="challenge" class="cre-challenge-section">
  <div class="cre-challenge-container">
    <span class="section-label">THE CHALLENGE</span>
    <h2 class="cre-challenge-headline">
      Speed vs. accuracy in field service operations
    </h2>
    <p class="cre-challenge-subheadline">
      Trade services move fast out of necessity. Customers call with urgent needs. Weather windows are tight. Equipment downtime costs money. 
      But most service companies are still running on phone calls, paper tickets, and disconnected systems that create delays and margin leakage.
    </p>

    <!-- Highlight Box -->
    <div class="cre-highlight-box">
      <p class="cre-highlight-text">
        "The average trade service company loses 18-28% of potential profit because they can't route crews efficiently and track time accurately."
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Challenge List -->
    <div class="cre-challenge-list-wrapper">
      <ul class="cre-challenge-list">
        <li><strong>Job dispatch is manual and inefficient</strong> across phone calls, text messages, and spreadsheets—making it impossible to route crews optimally and creating wasted travel time and delays.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer communication is fragmented</strong>, with job updates, status changes, and billing information scattered across email and phone calls instead of a unified channel.</li>
        <li><strong>Time tracking is disconnected from billing</strong>, requiring crews to log hours manually and office staff to re-enter data, creating gaps and delays in invoicing that extends cash flow cycles.</li>
        <li><strong>Job profitability is unknown until after completion</strong>, with no real-time visibility into labor costs, material usage, or margins until invoicing happens weeks later.</li>
        <li><strong>Service quality metrics are invisible</strong>, making it impossible to track first-time fix rates, customer satisfaction, or identify which technicians deliver best results.</li>
        <li><strong>Inventory and parts management is reactive</strong>, leading to technicians arriving without needed parts, creating callbacks and wasted trips instead of efficient first-time completion.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Stat Cards -->
    <div class="cre-stat-cards">
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">18-28%</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">profit lost</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">35+ hrs</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">weekly dispatch overhead</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">5-7 days</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">invoicing delay</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cre-challenge-section {
    background: #FFFFFF;
    padding: clamp(30px, 4vw, 50px) 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-headline {
    font-family: 'Figtree', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5vw, 56px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-subheadline {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-box {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border-left: 4px solid #0EA5E9;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-text {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #000000;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list-wrapper {
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 32px;
    font-size: 17px; /* Increased from 16px for better readability */
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li::before {
    content: '−';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li strong {
    font-size: 17px; /* Match parent font size */
    color: #000000;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .cre-stat-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-stat-card {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.2);
    padding: 32px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.4s ease;
  }

  .cre-stat-card:hover {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.4);
  }

  .cre-stat-number {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .cre-stat-label {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .cre-challenge-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 16px; /* Slightly smaller on tablet */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 16px; /* Match tablet size */
    }

    .cre-stat-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cre-challenge-section {
      padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px) 24px;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 15px; /* Original size on mobile for space efficiency */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 15px; /* Match mobile size */
    }

    .cre-highlight-box {
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .cre-stat-card {
      padding: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>


